Part I - (Dataset Exploration Title)¶

by Mtisunge Tupochere Malemia¶

Introduction¶

The prosper dataset is financial dataset that hasinformation on loans, borrowers, lenders, interest rates, reasons for borrowing, payment amount, payment period etc. Prosper or Prosper Marketplace Inc. is a San Francisco, California based company specializing in loans at low interest rates to the borrowers. in this project we analyse this data inorder to find different patterns that exist in the dataset. All analysis is done in python and presented in an HTML format.

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The dataset originally has 113937 rows and 81 columns. From this i will only pick features which will be needed for the analysis that i will do. There after i will go through the process of data wrangling.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The main features of interest in my dataset and their intepretation are as shown below:

1. **Term** :   The length of the loan expressed in months.<br>
2. **LoanStatus**:  The current status of the loan: Cancelled,  Chargedoff, Completed, Current, Defaulted,                                  FinalPaymentInProgress, PastDue. The PastDue status will be accompanied by a delinquency bucket.<br>
3.**BorrowerRate**: The Borrower's interest rate for this loan. <br>
4.**ProsperScore**: this feature estimates the probability of a loan going bad. A custom risk score built using historical                  Prosper data. The score ranges from 1-10, with 10 being the best, or lowest risk score.  Applicable for                        loans originated after July 2009.<br>
5.**ListingCategory**: This is the customers reason for getting the loan. The category of the listing that the borrower                      selected when posting their listing: 0 - Not Available, 1 - Debt Consolidation, 2 - Home Improvement,                          3 - Business, 4 - Personal Loan, 5 - Student Use, 6 - Auto, 7- Other, 8 - Baby&Adoption, 9 - Boat,                              10 - Cosmetic Procedure, 11 - Engagement Ring, 12 - Green Loans, 13 - Household Expenses,                                      14 - Large Purchases, 15 - Medical/Dental, 16 - Motorcycle, 17 - RV, 18 - Taxes, 19 - Vacation,                                20 - Wedding Loans<br>
6.**BorrowerState**: The two letter abbreviation of the state of the address of the borrower at the time the Listing was        created.<br>
7.**Occupation**: The Occupation selected by the Borrower at the time they created the listing.<br>
8.**EmploymentStatusDuration**: The length in months of the employment status at the time the listing was created.<br>
9.**IsBorrowerHomeowner**: A Borrower will be classified as a homowner if they have a mortgage on their credit profile <br>
10.**DebtToIncomeRatio**: this is a ratio of how much the borrower owes versus their monthtly earning. This value is capped       at 10.01 (any debt to income ratio larger than 1000% will be returned as 1001%).<br>
11.**IncomeRange**: The income range of the borrower at the time the listing was created.<br>
12.**StatedMonthlyIncome**: The monthly income the borrower stated at the time the listing was created.<br>
13.**LoanOriginalAmount**:  The origination amount of the loan.<br>
14.**MonthlyLoanPayment**:  The scheduled monthly loan payment.<br>
15.**EmployementStatus**: The employment status of the borrower at the time they posted the listing.<br>

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

the feature that will help most in the analysis in the original loan amount. Most analysis will be compared to this feature.

Question 1: What is the distribution of the debt to income ratio in the dataset?¶

the debit to income ratio is the ratio of borrowers debt and their monthly income. if the ratio is lower it means that the borrowers have less debt than their income. if the ratio is higher. i.e greater than 1 it would mean that the borrower has more debt than their monthly earning

Observation¶

The distribution is skewed to the right.from the graphs the debt to income ratio largely, is between 0 and 0.5. This means that for a majority of borrowers their "debt to income ratio" in low. This implies that most borrowers have less debt than their monthly income. However there are a few borrower whose "debt to income ratio" is above 1 and this is not a good sign

Conclusions¶

This exploration of Prosper loan data was aimed at identifying the different borrower motivations when applying for loans, including the different factors that may influence loan favorability.

  • In terms of borrower motivations, we found surprising results. Rather than take loans to start businesses or purchase assets, the largest population of people seemed to have taken loans to finance previously accrued debt. Debt consolidation also accounts for the highest loan amounts collected from the platform on average. Asides business purposes, borrowers seem to depend on huge loans to finance weddings, child adoptions, boat acquisitions, and the purchase of engagement rings
  • Borrowers who are employed, high earners and have homes are prefferes by londing institions. According to literature such categories of peopla are less likey to end up with bad debts that is why they are preffered.
